summary: This document is a fax machine activity log from the Palm Beach Police Department, covering the period from December 28, 2005, to January 24, 2006. It records numerous send and receive transactions, with some entries identified as related to an 'MRC INVESTIGATION IN FISA', indicating law enforcement communication activity during the investigation period.

events.title: Fax Communication Activity Period
events.description: A log of fax machine send and receive activity at the Palm Beach Police Department, showing frequent communication over this period.

keyFacts: The fax log shows active communication at the Palm Beach Police Department from late December 2005 through January 2006.
Multiple entries are specifically identified as related to an 'MRC INVESTIGATION IN FISA', suggesting official investigative activity.
The log records both successful transmissions (OK) and failed attempts (Busy, No Answer, No Fax Detected, Stop).
The document is part of the Epstein case files, indicating these communications may be relevant to the investigation into Jeffrey Epstein.
